Melt the butter with the olive oil in a frying pan and fry the onion and garlic until soft.Add the mushroom and cook until soft, then season well with salt and freshly ground black pepper.Add the white wine and cook to reduce by half.Add the stock and simmer for five minutes, then add the cream and parsley.Allow to cool slightly, then iquidise until smooth in a blender. Serve in a warm bowl, reheating if necessary.